    Phase 0 Sample Creation by Region for Ortho Spine

    phase0_create_sampled_by_region.Rd

    This function processes taxonomy and AAOS data, merging it with Census Bureau data to create a sampled dataset grouped by region for ortho spine. Outputs are saved as a CSV.

    phase0_create_sampled_by_region(
  taxonomy_and_aaos_tbl,
  census_bureau_tbl,
  output_csv_path = "ortho_spine/phase_0/sampled_by_region_ortho_spine.csv"
)

    Arguments

    taxonomy_and_aaos_tbl

    A tibble containing taxonomy and AAOS data.

    census_bureau_tbl

    A tibble containing Census Bureau data with regional information.

    output_csv_path

    The file path to save the sampled dataset. Defaults to "ortho_spine/phase_0/sampled_by_region_ortho_spine.csv".

    Value

    A tibble of sampled ortho spine records by region.

    Examples

    # Example 1: Basic usage with default output path
sampled_data <- phase0_create_sampled_by_region(taxonomy_and_aaos_tbl, census_bureau_tbl)
